 evolution of the rates, K-corrections, and non-Euclidean
 luminosity distance, which affect the detection rates of
 the most sensitive surveys. The number of detected events
 is calculated by means of a Monte Carlo method, using the
 various survey properties (depth, cadence, area) and
 realistic detection criteria that include a cut on the
 minimum variability of the transients during the survey and
 an assessment of host galaxy contamination. We find that
