  Abstract                 = {The long-term evolution of massive black hole binaries at
 the centers of galaxies is studied in a variety of physical
 regimes, with the aim of resolving the ``final parsec
 problem,'' i.e., how black hole binaries manage to shrink
 to separations at which emission of gravity waves becomes
 efficient. A binary ejects stars by the gravitational
 slingshot and carves out a loss cone in the host galaxy.
 Continued decay of the binary requires a refilling of the
