  Abstract                 = {If the stellar population of the bulge contains black
 holes formed in the final core collapse of ordinary stars
 with M>~30 Msolar, then about 25,000 stellar mass black
 holes should have migrated by dynamical friction into the
 central parsec of the Milky Way, forming a black hole
 cluster around the central supermassive black hole. These
 black holes can be captured by the central black hole when
