  Pages                    = {368-381},
  Volume                   = {628},

  Abstract                 = {The quasi-steady structure of supercritical accretion
 flows around a black hole is studied based on
 two-dimensional radiation-hydrodynamic (2D-RHD)
 simulations. The supercritical flow is composed of two
 parts: the disk region and the outflow regions above and
