 emission traces ongoing accretion. The results imply that
 jets in systems that have experienced recent active
 galactic nucleus (AGN) outbursts, in the last Ëœ107 yr, are
 `on' at least half of the time. Nuclear X-ray sources
 become more luminous with respect to the mechanical jet
 power as the mean accretion rate rises. We show that
 nuclear radiation exceeds the jet power when the mean
 accretion rate rises above a few per cent of the Eddington
