  Volume                   = {541},

  Abstract                 = {Aims: The study of tidal disruption flares from galactic
 nuclei has historically been hampered by a lack of high
 quality spectral observations taken around the peak of the
 outburst. Here we introduce the first results from a
 program designed to identify tidal disruption events at
 their peak by making near-real-time comparisons of the flux
 seen in XMM-Newton slew sources with that seen in ROSAT.
