 stellar evolution, can drive the inner stellar binaries to
 merge. We study the mergers of stellar binaries in the
 inner 0.1 pc of the GC caused by gravitational
 perturbations due to the MBH. We run a large set of Monte
 Carlo simulations that include the secular evolution of the
 orbits, general relativistic precession, tides and
 post-main-sequence stellar evolution. We find that about 13
 per cent of the initial binary population will have merged
