 compression of a star in a high-beta TDE. Although this
 signal is unlikely to be detectable for disruptions of
 main-sequence stars, the tidal disruption of a white dwarf
 by an intermediate mass black hole can produce a strong
 signal visible to Advanced LIGO at tens of megaparsecs.},
