 revealed a redshift of z = 0.19. At this redshift, the peak
 magnitude of the OT is close to -22.5, similar to the
 brightest super-luminous supernovae; however, the lack of
 identifiable spectral features makes the massive stellar
 death hypothesis less likely. A more plausible explanation
