 transient accretion onto intermediate-mass black holes at
 galactic centers following tidal disruption of stars in a
 gas-rich environment. We estimate the incidence of such
 events to be around 10-5 yr-1 for a galaxy with -21.3 < Mi
 < -18.5.},
