 clouds, and this type of interaction may have relevance for
 the paucity of extended radio jets in spiral galaxies.
 Slow, dense jets may be bent yet remain stable for fairly
 extended times, and such interactions can be responsible
 for some of the wide-angle tail and most of the ``dogleg''
